-------------------------------------------WHY API Security--------------------------------------------------------

API - Application Programming Interface

An application programming interface (API) is a way for two or more computer programs to communicate with each other. It is a type of software interface, 
offering a service to other pieces of software.A document or standard that describes how to build or use such a connection or interface is called an API specification.

Google map - Lyft
Venmo - WellsFargo
Kayak - United 
shared Externally.

Also companies use it internally.

Big Deal with API Security?

1.Explosive Growth  - AKAMAI (83%)
2.Major Attack Target - Gartner
3.High Profile Breaches - Coinbase,Peloton
4.Regulatory Compliance - PCI,GDPR.EU

BEING STOLEN?
Venmo payments,Bumble,linkedin,Experian API Expose

WHY ATTACKERS TARGET APIs
APIs:
*Direct Access to Sensitive Data
*Often "Over-permissioned"
*Vulnerable to logic flaws


Application ----> API ---->  Microservices
                             Web App 
                             Mobile App
                             Public API
                             Internal 
                             
                             
Classic Cyber Attack
Reconnaissance---------> Weaponize----------->Infiltration -------------->Laternal Movement--------->Privilege Escalation----------->BREACH

API ATTACK
